values:
Well, my little son Roan&nbsp;is almost 3 months old. He's beautiful! And growing and smiling and an absolute JOY! The new homemade formula is working wonders and his thriving. We need to find him a new pediatrician, but I am going to be optimistic... rather than stress about it. Daniel and Rob and I are trying to get rid of the negative energies in our home... catch up on things and think about renting a bigger&nbsp;place as Roan will soon need his&nbsp;own room.&nbsp; 

Roan met his great aunties and great grandmother yesterday, he was all&nbsp;smiles. It's been 10 years since&nbsp;Ben. I still feel&nbsp;his presence especially now with his litter brother here. &nbsp;My aunt said I should try for another one when Roan is a year. LOL we shall see. My grandmother said he was beautiful and said how happy she was that I was able to have another child. Amazing coming from a woman whom my husband describes as having a constant expression of having eaten cat shit. YEA... lol.&nbsp; 

Our youngest female cat Jasmine, has adopted Roan as her own practically and is never far from him. When he cries she meows at me to "do something... make it stop... wtf... " LOL I don't know I don't speak fluent feline. But it's cute as hell. The dogs are not threatened by him. Precious licks him when I tell her to give him kisses, Tink is careful how she jumps on the bed when I have him laying on it. I am amazed at our animals and how wonderfully sensitive and intuitive they are about the baby.&nbsp; 

Samhain is almost upon us, then Thanksgiving, then Hanukkah and then Yule... the holidays are here and I'm thankful for new friends and family. I cannot see for myself what the future will hold, and yes I am anxious about certain things, but I see the calm resolve and prosperity that awaits once we are through the storm. There were a lot of changes to our lives and family in this past year so the dust hasn't settled yet. But it will.&nbsp; 

I hadn't had a chance to update my LJ for a while, the baby wasn't giving me ANY free time not even with steady nap times, but he's getting better and a schedule for him has started to emerge and take form for us, which allows me the needed time to keep up with housework, homework, friends, email etc. I will post more pics of my beautiful baby boy later on in the week when I get the chance. :) 

I hope everyone is well and I send you my blessings
